HEADWORD: Preceptory
<hw>Pre*cep"to*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Preceptories</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL.
<ets>praeceptoria</ets> an estate assigned to a preceptor, from L.
<ets>praeceptor</ets> a commander, ruler, teacher, in LL., procurator,
